While you can always buy a pre-formed graham cracker pie shell, making it yourself is easy, and tastes way better! Grease the inside of a springform pan. You can use vegetable oil, or softened butter (our preference). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/ac/Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/ac/Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Mix the crumbs and softened butter together until well blended, then press over the bottom and sides of the pan. Place the pan in the refrigerator to chill and set while you make the batter. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c1/Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c1/Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

This is where your inner chef gets to come out and play. Combine the ricotta and cream cheese, beating well until smooth. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d2/Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d2/Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-4.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Fold in the remaining ingredients and continue beating until the mixture is smooth. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/21/Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-5.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/21/Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-5.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Bailey%27s-Cheesecake-Step-5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
